introduction: Case Walker is a star on the rise and shines through the screen with his heartfelt and charismatic performances.Walker can be seen in the critically acclaimed HBO Max show "The Other Two (2019)", written by former "Saturday Night Live (1975)" head writers Chris Kelly and Sarah Schneider. In 2018, Walker landed the lead role in "The Other Two" as Chase Dubek, the younger brother of Cary (Drew Tarver) and Brooke (Heléne Yorke), who is thrust into stardom after a viral Internet video. The show follows Cary and Brooke as they try to find their place in the world while wrestling with their feelings about their 13-year-old brother's sudden rise to fame. Ken Marino and Molly Shannon also star. The first season, which aired on Comedy Central in 2019, was deemed "The Year's Best New Comedy" by Entertainment Weekly.Walker can also be seen in the Paramount+ films "Monster High: The Movie (2022)" and "Monster High 2 (2023)", derived from the widely known Mattel property.When not performing, Walker enjoys rock climbing. He currently resides in Colorado.
